{"questionId":"5275567","questionHtml":"<p>A resistor of resistance <em>R</em> is connected to an alternating current power supply. The peak voltage across the resistor is <em>V</em><sub>0</sub>.</p>\n<p>What is the mean power dissipated by the resistor?</p>\n<p><br>A.&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><msup><msub><mi>V</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mn>2</mn></msup><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mrow><mi>R</mi></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>B.&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><msup><msub><mi>V</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>R</mi></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>C.&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><msup><msub><mi>V</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mn>2</mn></msup><mrow><mi>R</mi><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mrow></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>D.&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><msup><msub><mi>V</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mn>2</mn></msup><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>R</mi></mrow></mfrac></math></p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>D</p>","meta":{"questionId":"5275567","referenceCode":"23M.1.HL.TZ1.36","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"A resistor of resistance R is connected to an alternating current power supply. The peak voltage across the resistor is V0. What is the mean power dissipated by the resistor? A. V0","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"36","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Option B: Engineering physics"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}